4 SECTION 1.(g) Chapter 120 of the General Statutes is amended by adding a new
5 Article to read:
6 "Article 1B.
7 "Redistricting.
8 "§ 120-4.50. Definitions.
9 As used in this Article, unless the context requires otherwise, the following definitions shall
10 apply:
11 (1) Census Bureau. – The United States Bureau of the Census.
12 (2) Commission. – The North Carolina Citizens Redistricting Commission
13 established pursuant to G.S. 120-4.55.
14 (3) Communities of interest. – Contiguous and cohesive populations of persons
15 that share common social, economic, or policy interests. Communities of
16 interest shall not include common relationships with political parties or
17 political candidates. Communities of interest include, but are not limited to,
18 populations that share any of the following characteristics:
19 a. A racial, cultural, geographic, or ethnic identity.
20 b. A common history of marginalization or discrimination.
21 c. Natural resources.
22 d. Excessive damage from past or present natural disasters or pollution.
23 e. An organized decision-making body.
24 (4) Congressional districts or plans. – Districts or plans for the House of
25 Representatives of the United States Congress.
26 (5) Federal census. – The decennial census required by federal law to be
27 conducted by the Census Bureau in every year ending in zero.
28 (6) Final plan. – A plan adopted by the Commission to be used for the purpose of
29 nominating and electing identified representatives. In accordance with Section
30 25 of Article II of the North Carolina Constitution, final plans shall have the
31 force and effect of acts of the General Assembly.
32 (7) Ideal population. – The number determined by dividing the number of
33 members in a plan into the population of the State as reported in the federal
34 census.
35 (8) Identified representative. – A member of the Senate or House of
36 Representatives of the General Assembly or a member of the House of
37 Representatives of the United States Congress.
38 (9) Legislative districts or plans. – Districts or plans for the Senate and House of
39 Representatives of the General Assembly.
40 (10) Metropolitan or micropolitan statistical areas. – Areas of the State defined as
41 metropolitan or micropolitan statistical areas by the Office of Management
42 and Budget of the United States.
43 (11) Plan. – A plan for legislative or congressional reapportionment drawn in
44 accordance with Section 25 of Article II of the North Carolina Constitution
45 and this Article.
46 (12) Preliminary plan. – An initial plan released by the Commission for public
47 input at the beginning of the redistricting cycle.
48 (13) Proposed and alternative plans. – Plans released by the Commission following
49 public input.
50 (14) Public office. – Elective State, local, or federal office.
