28 (e) Term of Office. – The term of office for members of the Commission shall begin on
29 July 1 of each year ending in zero. The members shall continue in office for 10 years until their
30 successors are appointed and qualified.
31 (f) Chair. – The position of chair of the Commission shall rotate every three months,
32 following a schedule randomly generated at the beginning of the redistricting cycle. No two
33 members who share the same party affiliation, or lack thereof, shall serve as chair in the same
34 six-month period. No member shall serve as chair more than once in a 12-month period.
35 (g) Removal from Office. – A member of the Commission may be removed from office,
36 as follows:
37 (1) By the authority that appointed the member for any of the following:
38 a. Failure to comply with G.S. 120-4.65.
39 b. Ineligibility pursuant to subsection (b) of this section.
40 (2) By a vote of at least 11 members of the Commission, including at least one
41 commissioner appointed from the same sub-sub-subdivision of
42 sub-subdivision b. of subdivision (3) of subsection (c) of this section, in open
43 session at any duly held meeting, for any cause that renders the member
44 incapable or unfit to discharge the duties of the office, including neglect of
45 duty or gross misconduct. All Commission member votes on removal of a
46 member pursuant to this subdivision shall be recorded in the record.
47 (h) Vacancies. – Any vacancy occurring in the membership of the Commission shall be
48 filled in the manner prescribed in this section by the authority that made the initial appointment.
49 Vacancies shall be filled for the remainder of the unexpired term.
50 (i) Stipend. – Members of the Commission shall receive a stipend of one thousand two
51 hundred dollars ($1,200) for each month that the Commission meets. Beginning July 1, 2040,
