5 "§ 120-4.70. Redistricting criteria.
6 All plans shall meet the following goals, in order of priority:
7 (1) Each identified representative shall represent, as nearly as may be, an equal
8 number of inhabitants.
9 (2) Compliance with the North Carolina Constitution, State law, the Constitution
10 of the United States, including the equal protection clause of the Fourteenth
11 Amendment, and federal law, to ensure that everyone, including members of
12 minority groups, have an equal opportunity to elect representatives of their
13 choice. A plan shall not diminish or dilute the ability of a member of a
14 minority from electing a candidate of his or her choice, whether alone or in
15 coalition with others.
16 (3) In accordance with subdivisions (1) and (2) of this section, the population for
17 a legislative district shall be within five percent (5%) of the ideal population
18 for that district. Congressional districts shall each have a population that is as
19 nearly equal as practicable to the ideal population but in all cases within
20 one-tenth of one percent (0.1%) of the ideal population for that district.
21 (4) All districts shall be contiguous. Areas that meet only at the points of
22 adjoining corners are not contiguous.
23 (5) Minimizing the number of split communities of interest with the following
24 communities of interest prioritized above all others and in the following order:
25 a. Municipalities and census designated places.
26 b. Precincts.
27 c. Counties.
28 (6) The Commission shall not consider electoral results or political considerations
29 in the preparation of a preliminary, proposed, or alternative plan. In order to
30 ensure that each citizen of the State has substantially equal voting power on
31 the basis of party affiliation, the Commission shall evaluate every proposed
32 and alternative plan after the plan is created to avoid inadvertently diminishing
33 or diluting a voter's opportunity to aggregate with likeminded voters to elect
34 a governing majority based on party affiliation. Before adopting a final plan,
35 the Commission shall revise any plan that it deems to have violated this
36 subdivision to the minimum extent necessary to remedy that violation.
37 (7) Districts shall not favor or disfavor an incumbent, and the Commission shall
38 not consider member residency in the preparation of a plan.
39 (8) To the extent practicable, all districts shall be compact. Districts should not
40 bypass nearby communities for more distant communities.
41 "§ 120-4.75. Adoption of redistricting plans by the Commission.
42 (a) Duties. – The Commission shall adopt preliminary, proposed, alternative, and final
43 plans, as follows:
44 (1) If there are at least three members appointed to the Commission from each
45 sub-sub-subdivision of G.S. 120-4.55(c)(3)b., plans shall be adopted by a vote
46 of at least nine members composed of at least three members appointed to the
47 Commission from each sub-sub-subdivision of G.S. 120-4.55(c)(3)b.
48 (2) If there are not at least three members appointed to the Commission from each
49 sub-sub-subdivision of G.S. 120-4.55(c)(3)b., plans shall be adopted by a vote
50 of all of the following:
