30 (c) Time Line. – The Commission shall adopt all plans no later than October 1 of the year
31 following each federal census. Prior to the adoption of a plan, the Commission shall adhere to
32 the following maximum time line:
33 (1) Within 30 days of receipt of data from the Census Bureau, the Commission
34 shall hold at least 10 initial public hearings pursuant to G.S. 120-4.80.
35 (2) Within 50 days of receipt of data from the Census Bureau, the Commission
36 shall release to the public preliminary plans for revising the congressional and
37 legislative districts.
38 (3) Within 70 days of receipt of data from the Census Bureau, the Commission
39 shall hold at least an additional 10 public hearings pursuant to G.S. 120-4.80.
40 (4) Within 90 days of receipt of data from the Census Bureau, the Commission
41 shall release to the public all of the following:
42 a. Proposed plans for revising the congressional and legislative districts.
43 b. Alternative plans for revising the congressional and legislative
44 districts.
45 c. A summary of public input provided pursuant to G.S. 120-4.80.
46 (5) Within 110 days of receipt of data from the Census Bureau, the Commission
47 shall vote to adopt final plans from its proposed or alternative plans for
48 revising the congressional and legislative districts.
49 (6) If the Commission fails to adopt any plan pursuant to subdivision (5) of this
50 subsection, the Commission shall adhere to the following extended maximum
51 time line:
